title: Crock Pot Chicken Enchilada Casserole
directions: Put chicken breasts and te enchilada sauce in slow cooker on HIGH for 4h or LOW for 8h
Shred the chicken with 2 forks right in the slow cooker.
Cut the tortillas in to strips, add to chicken and sauce. Stir.
Add 1 cup of cheese and half the olives into the sauce and chicken mixture. Stir again.
Flatten the mixture slightly. Add the rest of the cheese and the olives on top.
Cook on low for about 40-60 minutes longer.
ingredients: 1 28 oz can enchilada sauce (red or green)
